  "text": "There are also limited data demonstrating successful treatment with an alternative anti-EGFR MoAb following a severe infusion reaction with one anti-EGFR MoAb. Saif et al. described two mCRC patients with severe infusion reactions to panitumumab who were successfully challenged with cetuximab [CITATION_1] , and three patients with severe hypersensitivity reactions to cetuximab who were successfully challenged with panitumumab [CITATION_2] . The two patients who were switched to cetuximab received premedication with prednisone and antihistamines, and were treated with cetuximab according to a prolonged infusion time and gradual dose escalation [CITATION_3] . None of the three patients successfully switched to panitumumab received pretreatment 100 .",
